<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="71" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1436,963,1061]" pageId="10" pageNumber="71">
Eighteen species are recognized mainly from the Oriental Region, four species and five subspecies of this genus occur in the Palaearctic Region (
<bibRefCitation author="Pagliano, G. &amp; Brothers, D. J. &amp; Cambra, R. &amp; Lelej, A. S. &amp; Lo Cascio, P. &amp; Matteini Palmerini, M. &amp; Scaramozzino, P. L. &amp; Williams, K. A. &amp; Romano, M." box="[515,746,999,1025]" pageId="10" pageNumber="71" pagination="5 - 425" refId="ref19407" refString="Pagliano, G., Brothers, D. J., Cambra, R., Lelej, A. S., Lo Cascio, P., Matteini Palmerini, M., Scaramozzino, P. L., Williams, K. A. &amp; Romano, M. (2020 [&quot; 2018 &quot;]) Checklist of names in Mutillidae (Hymenoptera), with illustrations of selected species. Bollettino del Museo Regionale di Scienze Naturali di Torino, 36 (1 - 2), 5 - 425." type="journal article" year="2020">
Pagliano 
<emphasis box="[622,679,999,1025]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="71">et al.</emphasis>
2020
</bibRefCitation>
). One widespread Mediterranean species with two subspecies is distributed in 
<collectingCountry box="[331,458,1035,1061]" name="Azerbaijan" pageId="10" pageNumber="71">Azerbaijan</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
